Package actions

Class Summary
AboutingAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "About..." component, it shows message with information about the application and author of application.
AddingArcAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Add Arc" component, it adds new arc to the graph.
AddingImmediateTransitionAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Add Immediate Transition" component, it adds new Immediate Transition to the graph.
AddingPlaceAction Contains features of the transition of petri-net, Provides methods for setting and getting this features.
AddingTimeTransitionAction Contains features of the transition of petri-net, Provides methods for setting and getting this features.
CreatingAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "New" component, it saves current chart (if user wants it), and creates new empty chart, which has only one new empty row in the table.
DrawerKeyListener This class listens the keys press, if key is DEL it deletes active element.
DrawerMouseListener This class listens the mouse click, it performs adding, deleting, replacing Elements of Petri-net.
ExitingAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Exit" component, it saves current chart if user wants and terminates the application.
ExportingAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Export..." component, it saves current chart as image file to a disk.
HelpingAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Context help..." component, it tries to open help-file in the browser.
ModelEditorAction Created by IntelliJ IDEA.
ModelEmulationAction  
ModelTreeAction  
OpeningAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Open..." component, it saves current chart (if user wants it), and opens a specified legacy chart from xml-file.
RedoAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Redo" component, it re-do one operation of CommandStack.
SavingAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Save as..." component, it saves the current chart as xml-file to a disk.
UndoAction Action, which is occurred when user clicks "Undo" component, it undo one operation of CommandStack.
